A vintage 1970s technical illustration style image depicting a large, warm-toned filing cabinet drawer pulled open, revealing not traditional folders but dozens of glowing, self-contained capsules or orbs, each containing miniature complete worlds with tiny landscapes, objects, and data visualizations floating inside them. The capsules are arranged organically, some connected by delicate golden threads suggesting optional relationships. The background shows faded blueprint paper with subtle grid patterns. Warm amber, cream, and burnt orange color palette with subtle paper texture overlay. The composition suggests independence and completeness of each unit while existing harmoniously together in the same container.
